Description: Add libnvidia-ml-dev build-dep and drop apt libpmix-dev.
 NVML dev headers enable --with-nvml=/usr/local/cuda configure flag so
 slurmd links libnvidia-ml.so at runtime. libpmix-dev is removed
 because PMIx is provided by the AWS EFA installer's OMPI5 tree at
 /opt/amazon/openmpi5 (see debian/rules --with-pmix= patch). Shipping
 both apt libpmix and OMPI5 libpmix would create an ABI-conflicting
 second PMIx tree.
Author: meshy-dev
Forwarded: not-needed
Last-Update: 2026-04-19
--- a/debian/control
+++ b/debian/control
@@ -14,6 +14,7 @@ Build-Depends:
  libgtk2.0-dev,
  libhdf5-dev,
  libhttp-parser-dev,
+ libnvidia-ml-dev,
  libhwloc-dev,
  libipmimonitoring-dev,
  libjson-c-dev,
@@ -25,7 +26,6 @@ Build-Depends:
  libncurses-dev,
  libpam0g-dev,
  libperl-dev,
- libpmix-dev,
  librdkafka-dev,
  librrd-dev,
  libyaml-dev,
